&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Therapeutic Support Service Nurse to work within the Therapeutic Support Services within the in-patient Learning Disability Service in Bryn Y Neuadd Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves working within the Therapeutic Support Services providing nursing interventions and activities and meaningful occupation for people who suffer from a variety of mental/ Physical illness&#39; to help gain an understanding of illness and develop coping strategies to help them cope better when discharged back into the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 1st December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jane Williams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therapeutic Support Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jane.williams8@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
